x4freetext: Last checking has been done.
Ca-40,Ca-42,Ca-44,Ca-48 and Ti-48 were Used As Target.
The Targets are 21 mm High and 6 mm Wide. Their
Thicknesses are About 200 Mg/Cm**2.
All of Them Consist of Isotopically Enriched Isotopes-
. Authors` Purpose was to Deduce the Neutron
Density Parameters from a Comparision Between the
Experimental Angular Distributions and Those Calculated
Using the Glauber Theory, and the Charge Distributions
Being Measured by Electron Scattering.
. Two Six-Hold Scintillator Telescopes.
The Presented Results are Corrected For the Angular
Resolution (0.36 DEGREE FWHM) Which Takes Into Account
The Angular Resolution of the Experimental Set Up and
The Finite Size of the Angular Bins.
The Analysis System, Consisting of a
Dipole, Five Quadrupoles and Two Sextupoles, Allows One
To Control the Energy Dispersion and the Focussing
Parameters of the Beam on the Target.
*En-Rsl-Fw*.Energy Resolution.
The Errors in the Relative Ca-40, Ca-42, Ca-44,
Ca-48  and  Ti-48  Differential  Cross  Sections do not
Exceed 3%.
